Sree bOdhAyanamahar^Shi praNItAni mahAnyAsa sUtrANi
========================

Here bOdhAyanamahar^Shi is giving the mahanyaasa in a capsule form. 
He is directly teaching the mahanyaasa method (vidhiM vyAKyAsyAmaH). 

OM athAtaH pa~jcAMgarudrANAM nyAsapUr^vakaM japahOmAr^canABiShEkavidhiM vyAKyAsyAmaH ||
( pa~jcAMgarudrasya ayamar^tthaH pa~jcaprakArAH aMganyAsAH yEShu tE pa~jcAMga rudrAH | EvaM ShaDaMgarudrasyApi ShaTprakArAH aMganyAsAH yasya saH ityar^tthaH | tatra SiKAdyastraparyantaM EkatriMSadaMganyAsaH digbandha sahitaH prathamaH)

nyAsam 1 - (SiKAdyastraparyantaM EkatriMSadaMganyAsaH digbandha sahitaH prathamaH)
=======
1. yAtE rudrEti SiKAyAM | asmin^ mahatyar^NNava iti Sirasi |
sahasrANIti lalATE | ha(gm)saH SuciShaditi BruvOr^maddhyE |
tryaMbakaM yajAmahE iti nEtrayOH |  namaH srutyAyEti kar^NNayOH |
mAnastOka iti nAsikAyAM | avatatyEti muKE | nIlagrIvau dvau kaNThE | 
namastE astvAyudhAyEti bAhvOH | yA tE hEtirityupabAhvOH |  
pariNO rudrasya hEtiriti maNibandhayOH |  yE tIr^tthAnIti hastayOH | 
sadyOjAtamiti pa~jcAnuvAkAn^ pa~jcasvaMgulIShu |   
namO vaH kirikEBya iti hRudayE |  namO gaNEBya iti pRuShThE |   
namO hiraNyabAhava iti pAr^SvayOH | vijyaM dhanuriti jaTharE |   
hiraNyagar^Ba iti nABau | mIDhUShTamEti kaTyAM |   
yE BUtAnAmadhipataya iti guhyE | yE annEShvityaNDayOH |
saSirA jAtavEdA ityapAnE | mAnO mahAntamityur^vOH | 
EShatE rudra BAga iti jAnvOH | sa(gm)sRuShTajiditi jaMGayOH |
viSvaM BUtamiti gul^phayOH | yE pathAmiti pAdayOH | 
addhyavOchaditi kavacaM | namO bil^mina ityupakavacaM |
namO astu nIlagrIvAyEti tRutIyaM nEtraM | 
pramu~jca dhanvana ityastraM | ya EtAvantaScEti digbandhaH ||

nyAsam 2 - (mUr^ddhAdipAdAntaM daSAM~gganyAsaH dvitIyaH)
=======

2. OM namO BagavatE rudrAyEti namaskArAn^ nyasEt | 

i) OM~gkAraM mUr^ddhni vinyasya nakAraM nAsikAgrataH | 
mOkAraM tU lalATE vai BakAraM muKamaddhyataH || 

ii) gakAraM kaNDadESE tu vakAraM hRudi vinyasEt | 
    tEkAraM dakShiNE hastE rukAraM vAmatO nyasEt || 

iii) drAkAraM nABidESE tu yakAraM pAdayOr^ nyasEt || 

nyAsam 3 - pAdAdimUr^ddhAntaM pa~jcAMganyAsaH tRutIyaH
=========
3   i) sadyaM ca pAdayOr^nyasya vAmaM nyasyOrumaddhyataH |
	aGOraM hRudi vinyasya muKE tat puruShaM nyasEt || 

     ii) ISAnaM mUr^ddhani vinyasya haMsO nAmasadASivaH |
	 haMsa haMsEti yO brUyAt haMsO nAma sadASivaH | 

     iii) EvaM nyAsavidhiM kRutvA tataH saMpuTamAraBEt | 

     iv)  trAtAramindraM, tvaMnO agnE, sugaM naH panthAM, asunvantaM, tatvA yAmi, AnO niyudBiH | 
           vaya(gm)sOma, tamISAnaM, asmE rudrA, syOnApRuthivItyEtat saMpuTaM indrAdi dikShU vinyasya
           EvamEvAtmani ShODaSaraudrIkaraNaM kRutvA viBUrasItyanuvAkEna sAnuSha~ggENa || 

      v)  tvagasthigataiH sar^vapApaiH pramucyatE sar^vaBUtEShvaparAjitO Bavati |  
           tatO BUtaprEta piSAca brahmarAkShasa yakSha yamadUta SAkinI DAkinI sar^pa SvApada vRuScika taskarAdyUpadravAdyUpaGAtAH ||

      vi) sar^vE (grahAH) jvalantaM paSyantu |   mAM rakShantu | 

nyAsam 4 - guhyAdimastakAnta ShaDaMganyAsaH catur^tthaH
4   	manOjyOtiH, abOddhyagniH, agnir^mUr^ddhA, mUr^ddhAnaM, mar^mANi tE, jAtavEdA, 
iti guhya-nABi-hRudaya-kaNTha-muKa-SirAMsyaBimantrya AtmarakShA kar^ttavyA brahmAtmanvadasRujatEtyanuvAkEna | 
 
nyAsam 5 - hRudayAdya strAntaM ShaDaMganyAsaH pa~jcamaH
=======
5) 	Sivasa~gkal^paM hRudayaM, puruShasUktaM SiraH, uttaranArAyaNaM SiKA, apratirathaM kavacaM, pratipuruShadvayaM
	nEtraM, SatarudriyamityastraM | 

       korvai for Sivasa~gkal^paM
       1.  yEnEdaM, yEna kar^mANi, yEnakar^mANyapasO, yat praj~jAnagM, suShArathir^, yasminnRucO, yadatra ShaShThaM, yajjAgratO, yEnEdaM, yEna dyauH pRuthivI daSa |

	2.  yE manO hRudaya, macintya, mEkA ca, yE pa~jca, vEdAhamEtaM, yasyEdaM dhIrAH, parAt parataraM caiva, 
parAt paratarO brahmA, yA vEdAdiShu, yO vai dEvaM daSa |

	3.  prayatO, yO&sau, gOBir^ juShTaM, kailAsa SiKarE, tryaMbakaM, viSvataScakShu, ScaturO vEdAn, 
mAnO mahAnta, mmAnastOka, Ruta(gm) satyaM daSa |

	4.  kad rudrAya, brahmajaj~jAnaM, yaH prANatO, ya AtmadA, yO rudrO, gandhadvArAM, ya ida(gm) Sivasa~gkal^pa(gm) saptatri(gm)Sat.

pa~jcAMgaM sakRutjapEt - ha(gm)saH SuciShat,  pratadviShNuH, tryaMbakaM, tatsavitur^vRuNImahE, viShNur^ yOnimiti | 

	aShTAMgaM praNamya - hiraNyagar^BO, yaH prANatO, 	brahmajaj~jAnaM, mahIdauH, upaSvAsaya, agnE naya,
yAtE agnE, imaM yama ityaShTA~ggaM praNamya | 

	athAtmAnaM SivAtmAnaM SrIrudrarUpaM dhyAyEt | 
	(*athAtmAnaM rudrarUpaM dhyAyEt pa~jcamuKaM SivaM |  iti pAThAntaraM| ) 

	i)	SuddhasphaTikasa~gkASaM trinEtraM pa~jcavaktrakaM
		gaM~ggAdharaM daSaBujaM sar^vvABaraNa BUShitaM |

	ii) 	nIlagrIvaM SaSA~gkA~gkaM nAgayaj~jOpavItinaM
		vyAGracar^mmOttarIyaM ca varENyamaBayapradaM | 

	iii) 	kamaNDalvakShasUtrE ca dadhAnaM SUlapANinaM
		jvalantaM pi~ggaLajaTaM SiKAmaddhyOdadhAriNaM

	iv)	amRutEnAplutaM hRuShTaM divyaBOgasamanvitaM
		digdEvatA samAyuktaM surAsuranamaskRutaM| 

	v) 	nityaM ca SASvataM SuddhaM dhruvamakSharamavyayaM
		sar^vavyApinamISAnaM rudraM vai viSvarUpiNaM |
		EvaM dhyAtvA dvijaH samRuk tatO yajanamAraBEt | 

	athAtO rudrasnAnAr^canABiShEkavidhiM vyAKyAsyAmaH ||

	Adita Eva tIr^tthE snAtvA, udEtya ahataM vAsaH paridhAya,
	SuciH prayatO brahmacArI SuklavAsAH, ISAnasya pratikRutiM
	kRutvA tasya dakShiNApratyagdESE tanmuKaH sthitvA, Atmani
	dEvatAH sthApayEt | 

nyAsam 6 - ayaM ShaShThaH nyAsaH

6) prajananE brahmA tiShThatu | pAdayOH viShNustiShThatu |  
hastayOH harastiShThatu | bAhvOrindrastiShThatu |   
jaTharE agnistiShThatu | hRudayE SivastiShThatu |   
kaNThE vasavastiShThantu | vaktrE saraswatI tiShThatu |
nAsikayOr^vAyu stiShThatu | nayanayOScandrAdityau stiShThatAM | 
kar^NNayOraSvinau stiShThatAM |  lalATE rudrAstiShThantu |
mUr^ddhanyAdityAstiShThantu | Sirasi mahAdEvastiShThatu |
SiKAyAM vAmadEvastiShThatu | pRuShThE pinAkI stiShThatu | 
purataH SUlI stiShThatu | pAr^SvayOH SivASa~gkarau stiShThatAM |
sar^vatO vAyu stiShThatu | tatO bahIH sar^vatO&gnir^ jvAlAmAlAparivRutastiShThatu | 
sar^vvEShva~ggEShu sar^vAdEvatA yathAsthAnaM tiShThantu |  mAM (sakuTuMbaM) rakShantu | 

agnir^mmE vAci Srita iti yathAliMgaM aMgAni saMspRuSya AtmAnaM gandhapuShpadhUpadIpa naivEdyaiH mAnasaiH  ArAdhayEt | 

athainaM prasAdayEt | 

ArAdhitO manuShyaistvaM siddhair^ dEvAsurAdiBiH |
ArAdhayAmi BaktyA tvA&nugrahANa (tvAM mAM gRuhANa) mahESvara | 

AtvA vahantu harayaH sacEtasaH SvEtairaSvaiH sahakEtumadBiH | 
vAtAjitair^ balavadBiH manOjavairAyAhi SIGraM mama havyAya Sar^vvOM |   
tryaMbakamiti ca, ityAvAhayati, sthApitE tu na AvAhanaM| 

atha AsanaM | dadAti sadyO jAtamiti | BavE Bava iti pAdyaM | 
BavOdBAvAya namaH ityar^ghyaM | vAmadEvAya namaH ityAcamanIyaM | 
athainaM snapayati |   
ApO hiShThAdiBiH tisRuBiH, hiraNya var^NNA iti, pavamAnaH suvar^janaH ityanuvAkEna mAr^jayitvA, 
sar^vO vai rudraH, kayA naScitraH, apO vA id(gm) sar^vvaM ityEtaiSca, 
vAmadEvAya namaH iti vastraM, jyEShThAya namaH ityupavItaM, rudrAya namaH ityAcamanIyaM,
praNavEna BUShaNaM, kAlAya namaH iti gandhaM, kalavikaraNAya namaH ityakShatAn^, 
balavikaraNAya namaH iti puShpaM, balAya namaH itidhUpaM,
balapramathanAya namaH iti dIpaM, sar^vaBUtadamanAya namaH iti naivEdyaM,
manOnmanAya namaH iti tAMbUlaM dadAti | 

athAsmai aShTaBir^mmantraiH aShTau puShpANi dadAti 'BavAya dEvAyanamaH' ityAdi |   
athAsya aghOratanUrUpatiShThatE aGOrEByO&thaGOrEByaH iti,
atha rudragAyatrIM japEt, tat puruShAya vidmaha iti SatakRutvaH
aparimita kRutvaH vA daSavAraM vA |  
athainaM ASiShamASAstE,  ISAnaH sar^vva vidyAnAM iti | 

athasya mUr^ddhani hiraNyakalaSEna santatadhArAM niShi~jcEt | 
madhunA sar^piShA payasA cEkShurasEna AmrarasEna vA nALikErOdakEna
vA tadalABE udakEna vA namastE rudramanyava ityEkAdaSAnuvAkAn^ japEt | 
japAntE agnAviShNu sajOShasEtyEkAdaSAnuvAkAn^  pratyEkamEkamEkaM japEt | 
sar^vEShAM pArE punarArAdhayEt uttamArAdhanEna | 

tEna aBiShiktOdakEna akShIByAM ityanuvAkEna ab^^li~ggAdiBiScha A pAdAt saMspRuSya pApakShayAr^tthI vyAdhivimOkShAr^tthI SrIkAmaH SAntikAmaH puShTikAmaH tuShTikAmaH AyuShkAmaH ArOgyakAmaH
EvaM kuryAt |  EvaM kUr^van^ siddhimavApnOti | 

AcAryAya dakShiNAM dadAti | daSa gAH savatsAH suvar^NNaBUShitAH vRuShaBaikAdaSAH tadalABE EkAM gAM dadyAt |   EkAdaSa brAhmaNAn^ BOjayEt | aSvamEdhakratusahasraphalamavApnOtItyAha BagavAn^ bOdhAyanaH| 

|| iti bOdhAyana mahar^Shi praNItAni mahAnYAsasUtrANi || 

